article.headline: Wagner 75, Robert Morris 68
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Maurice Carter scored 28 points, including four 3-pointers, as Robert Morris beat Wagner 75-68 on Saturday night. Carter made 10-of-16 shots from the field and missed one of five free throws to help the Colonials (10-10, 7-4 Northeast Conference) win their second game in a row and close out their two-game homestand. Wagner (7-13, 4-6) was hampered by 34.3 percent shooting from the field (23 of 67), including 4-for-21 shooting from 3-point range. But the Seahawks came back after halftime, and briefly held a 46-41 lead. Robert Morris' Chaz McCrommon scored 22 points, including one 3-pointer, while Aaron Thomas scored 14 points, including four 3-pointers.
